00:18:49,063 --> 00:18:51,113
Come on, you can't live off your parents your whole life.

238
00:18:51,113 --> 00:18:54,305
I know that. That's why I was getting married.

239
00:18:54,305 --> 00:18:55,977
Give her a break.

240
00:18:55,977 --> 00:19:02,002
It's hard being on your own for the first time.

241
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Thank you.

242
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're welcome.

243
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I remember when I first came to this city.

244
00:19:02,002 --> 00:19:02,687
I was 14.

245
00:19:02,687 --> 00:19:06,235
My mom had just killed herself and my stepdad was back in prison.

246
00:19:06,235 --> 00:19:07,958
And I got here and I didn't know anybody.

247
00:19:07,958 --> 00:19:13,277
And I ended up living with this albino guy who was, like, cleaning windshields outside Port Authority.

248
00:19:13,277 --> 00:19:16,523
And then he killed himself.

249
00:19:16,523 --> 00:19:18,332
And then I found aromatherapy.

250
00:19:18,332 --> 00:19:24,437
So, believe me, I know exactly how you feel.

251
00:19:24,437 --> 00:19:36,895
The word you're looking for is… anyway.

252
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I don't think so.

253
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Oh, come on.

254
00:19:36,895 --> 00:19:45,953
Cut, cut, cut…

255
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hey!

256
00:19:45,953 --> 00:19:48,659
Welcome to the real world!&nbsp; It sucks.

257
00:19:48,659 --> 00:19:59,160
You're gonna love it.

258
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That's it.

259
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:01,168
